result.formatted_address: 20-36 Wharf Rd, North Point, Hong Kong
result.name: Korea Restaurant

reviews.text: Very good quality of food with lots of selection.
Resonable price with good food
Great value and taste good!

The restaurant name is actually Korea restaurant and not Koryo. It is clean and spacious and the waiters are friendly. The selection of meat and vegetables is vast and fresh. The meat is tender and marinated well. The kimchi and other Korean veg are worthy of mention. Also they have a big pot of chicken and  ginseng soup which is delicious. The price for buffet is 188 for adults and 4 small bottles of Tsingtoa are 39, while a large bottle is 25 (plus10% service).
The only thing that they could improve is the selection of dessert, maybe add ice cream or some cake.

Desserts are lacking, as in, hardly anything worthy outside a hospital, but... Lots of meat, lots of veggies. BBQ. If you want good BBQ, then this place is better for selection than Hon Wo. Variety of marinated meats, eggplant, zucchini, onion, mushroom, corn, potato, pumpkin... Veggie salads. Sauces are lacking too, not authentic Korean, but you can rig your own with their cooking miso and la-yu

reviews.text: 位於明輝商場樓上舖，經營多年，設限時任食自助餐 (日本稱放題)，建議訂位。
Very good quality of food with lots of selection.
飲品要另外收費。
舊式韓國燒烤, 自己夾食物, 質數都好好
